cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper deals with the analysis of large-scale datasets of information cascades in online social media, focusing on their structural patterns and their correlations with dynamics and semantics. The paper proposes a ten-dimensional metric to quantify the structural characteristics of information cascades, and analyzes the high-order structural patterns of information cascades. The paper also evaluates to what extent the structural features of information cascades can explain its dynamic patterns and semantics. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DL (Machine Learning).
